  <h1>
   view_set_wport
  </h1>
  This function can be used to set the width of the given view port. You give the view port index (from 0 to 7) and the new width to use.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">view_set_wport(view_port, w)
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      view_port
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The view port to target (0 - 7)
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      w
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The new width (in pixels)
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if view_get_wport(0) != (display_get_width () / 2)
{
    view_set_wport(0, display_get_width() / 2);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check the width of the view port[0] and if it is not half of the display width it is set to that value.
 </body>
